up%20valued%20at%20%24295%20million.%3Cp%3EFlipkart%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPunit%20Soni%20worked%20at%20Google%2C%20Motorola%20and%20as%20the%20chief%20product%20officer%20at%20Flipkart%20in%20India.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20couldn't%20shake%20the%20desire%20to%20build%20a%20company%20of%20his%20own%20and%20launched%20a%20health%20tech%20startup.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESonit%20said%20life%20as%20a%20founder%20can%20be%20lonely%20and%20has%20extremes%2C%20but%20feels%20his%20work%20is%20meaningful.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Punit%20Soni%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.suki.ai%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3ESuki%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20an%20AI%20voice%20solution%20for%20healthcare%20professionals%20valued%20at%20%24295%20million.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20Soni's%20employment%20with%20documents.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBorn%20to%20a%20nuclear%20scientist%20father%20and%20a%20psychologist%20mother%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20my%20early%20life%20was%20steeped%20in%20academia.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20got%20a%20degree%20in%20engineering%20at%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20Kurukshetra%20in%201998%20and%20a%20master's%20in%20electrical%20engineering%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Wyoming%20in%201998.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20worked%20as%20a%20quality%20assurance%20engineer%20in%20semiconductors%20before%20pursuing%20an%20MBA%20at%20The%20Wharton%20School%20in%202007.%20After%20my%20MBA%2C%20I%20considered%20private%20equity%20or%20consulting%2C%20but%20Silicon%20Valley's%20siren%20call%20brought%20me%20back%20to%20tech.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227b3802ef-bc9a-41de-ad08-9d28e37423ad%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20career%20in%20Big%20Tech%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20June%202007%2C%20I%20applied%20to%20Google%20as%20a%20product%20manager.%20At%20Google%2C%20I%20spearheaded%20Google%2B%20Games%20and%20mobile%20initiatives.%20I%20helped%20grow%20the%20mobile%20team%20and%20launched%20features%20like%20Mobile%20Hangouts%20and%20Instant%20Upload.%20Over%20those%20five%20years%2C%20I%20learned%20about%20scaling%20products%20and%20seeing%20failure%20as%20an%20opportunity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20left%20Google%20in%20August%202012%20for%20an%20executive%20role%20at%20Motorola%20as%20VP%20of%20product%20management.%20While%20at%20Motorola%2C%20I%20gained%20insight%20into%20the%20e-commerce%20market%20in%20India%2C%20which%20prompted%20me%20to%20eventually%20leave%20and%20move%20to%20Bangalore.%20I%20began%20my%20role%20as%20chief%20product%20officer%20at%20Flipkart%20in%20India's%20tech%20hub.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20a%20decade%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20all%20the%20roles%20at%20the%20time%20were%20the%20same%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20exercise%20a%20different%20part%20of%20my%20brain.%20Being%20in%20India%20and%20adjusting%20to%20a%20different%20workforce%20was%20an%20interesting%20challenge.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20Flipkart%2C%20I%20was%20responsible%20for%20all%20product%20initiatives%20and%20helped%20scale%20the%20company.%20I%20left%20in%202016%2C%20and%20Flipkart%20was%20acquired%20by%20Walmart%20in%202018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a23f143c-4922-46bd-b93f-085f5fbaccce%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20couldn't%20ignore%20the%20entrepreneurial%20itch%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20working%20at%20tech%20giants%20and%20successful%20startups%2C%20the%20entrepreneurial%20itch%20I'd%20had%20since%20my%20early%20days%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20could%20no%20longer%20be%20ignored.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20at%20Motorola%2C%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20build%20Moto%20X%2C%20which%20had%20its%20first%20always-on%20voice%20interface.%20Building%20this%20software%20made%20me%20aware%20that%20voice%20was%20going%20to%20be%20the%20default%20for%20most%20devices.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20conversations%20around%20the%20artificial%20intelligence%20were%20just%20starting%2C%20but%20these%20insights%20helped%20me%20develop%20my%20company%20Suki.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20wanted%20to%20build%20something%20that%20made%20healthcare%20tech%20assistive%20and%20invisible%2C%20so%20doctors%20could%20focus%20on%20patients.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20of%20my%20former%20Google%20colleagues%20who%20were%20leaving%20the%20company%20were%20going%20into%20education%20or%20healthcare.%20I%20saw%20healthcare%20as%20an%20area%20where%20I%20could%20make%20an%20impact.%20I%20came%20up%20with%20the%20idea%20for%20Suki%20and%20started%20building%20the%20foundational%20elements%20while%20in%20India.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20family%20was%20sick%20and%20tired%20of%20me%20complaining%20about%20starting%20something%20new%20and%20encouraged%20me%20to%20leave%20Big%20Tech%20to%20do%20it%20myself.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228161a42f-ddd1-4a6f-8dd0-48d90f6c46af%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20was%20a%20big%20shift%20going%20from%20employee%20to%20founder%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20left%20Flipkart%20in%202016%20and%20returned%20to%20the%20States%20to%20spend%20the%20next%20six%20months%20settling%20down.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20moved%20houses%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20adjust%20to%20a%20new%20area%20and%20new%20schools%20for%20my%20kids.%20I%20was%20lucky%20enough%20to%20have%20saved%20resources%20that%20helped%20me%20launch%20Suki%2C%20so%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20change%20too%20much%20of%20my%20lifestyle.%20I%20was%20also%20mentally%20prepared%2C%20knowing%20that%20there%20were%20not%20going%20to%20be%20that%20many%20incoming%20resources%20or%20revenue%20at%20the%20start%20of%20a%20new%20business%20venture.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBecoming%20a%20founder%20impacts%20your%20emotional%20and%20mental%20health.%20For%20the%20first%20few%20years%2C%20I%20worked%20off%20fumes%20and%20juggled%20many%20hats.%20No%20day%20was%20the%20same.%20Whereas%20in%20Big%20Tech%2C%20I%20had%20more%20of%20an%20established%20work%20routine.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20Google%20and%20Flipkart%2C%20I%20was%20a%20senior%20executive%20with%20many%20people%20reporting%20to%20me%2C%20but%20at%20Suki%2C%20I%20had%20to%20start%20from%20the%20bottom%20to%20reassess%20the%20skills%20I%20was%20good%20at%20and%20learn%20new%20ones%20to%20help%20move%20the%20company%20forward.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20best%20part%20of%20starting%20my%20own%20company%20is%20the%20pride%20I%20feel%20in%20building%20something%20that%20has%20a%20real%20impact.%20Over%20350%20healthcare%20systems%20are%20using%20Suki%20to%20help%20doctors%20focus%20on%20patient%20care.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20also%20really%20value%20the%20control%20and%20autonomy%20I%20have%20now%20compared%20to%20my%20prior%20careers%20in%20Big%20Tech.%20I%20want%20to%20create%20a%20drama-free%20environment%20at%20Suki%20with%20no%20internal%20political%20hierarchies.%20I%20care%20about%20our%20combined%20collective%20success.%20I%20want%20Suki%20to%20be%20a%20workplace%20where%20we%20give%20each%20other%20feedback%20and%20improve%20each%20other's%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFinancially%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20any%20dramatic%20changes%20moving%20from%20being%20an%20employee%20to%20a%20founder%20because%20I%20always%20maintained%20a%20middle-class%20lifestyle.%20However%2C%20it's%20still%20uncomfortable%20building%20something%20because%20you%20have%20to%20use%20more%20money%20than%20you're%20making.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216eb516c-e4b6-4f15-92f3-611b40d673ef%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ELife%20as%20a%20CEO%20has%20extremes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20days%20being%20a%20CEO%20is%20empowering%2C%20while%20others%20are%20exhausting%20and%20frustrating.%20It%20can%20feel%20like%20you're%20on%20a%20treadmill%20that%20never%20stops.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEntrepreneurship%20is%20also%20lonely%2C%20and%20early%20on%2C%20I%20had%20to%20face%20failures%20and%20overcome%20them.%20I%20was%20a%20poor%20CEO%20for%20the%20first%20two%20or%20three%20years%20because%20I%20couldn't%20manage%20my%20emotional%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI've%20made%20every%20founder%20mistake%20because%20of%20my%20challenges%20with%20regulating%20my%20emotions.%20I've%20had%20countless%20sleepless%20nights%2C%20lost%20my%20temper%2C%20let%20go%20of%20people%2C%20people%20have%20let%20go%20of%20me%2C%20and%20even%20lost%20friendships.%20The%20key%20lesson%20I%20learned%20was%20how%20to%20react%20to%20these%20situations%20constructively%20while%20moving%20forward.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20learned%20that%20a%20good%20CEO%20knows%20how%20to%20channel%20their%20energy%2C%20learn%20relationship%20management%2C%20and%20invest%20in%20the%20right%20operations%20and%20people.%20%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20my%20major%20challenges%20was%20finding%20the%20right%20people.%20My%20advice%20is%20to%20hire%20candidates%20who%20are%20better%20than%20you%20in%20every%20area.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20romanticize%20startup%20life.%20Building%20a%20company%20is%20not%20a%20financial%20or%20professional%20decision%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20romantic%20one.%20You%20need%20to%20love%20your%20idea%20and%20have%20the%20emotional%20intelligence%20and%20energy%20to%20see%20it%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20I%20don't%20wish%20entrepreneurship%20on%20anybody.%20It's%20a%20risky%20financial%20decision%20to%20leave%20a%20stable%20job.%20But%20%3Cspan%3EI%20love%20what%20I'm%20doing%20most%20days.%20The%20idea%20of%20building%20something%20meaningful%20from%20the%20ground%20up%20was%20incredibly%20important%20to%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-big-tech-job-startup-founder-ai-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739968063000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b4d0347bb3f854015d2638%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-big-tech-job-startup-founder-ai-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Punit%20Soni%20worked%20at%20Google%2C%20Motorola%20and%20Flipkart%20before%20quitting%20to%20pursue%20entrepeneurship.%20He%20said%20life%20as%20a%20founder%20is%20lonely%20and%20has%20extremes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Pooja%20Shah)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-big-tech-job-startup-founder-ai-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shraddha%20to%20star%20in%20'Sanam%20Teri%20Kasam%202'%3B%20netizens%20REACT%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739967978000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-118388268%2Cimgsize-52702.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fshraddha-kapoor-might-replace-pakistani-actress-mawra-hocane-in-sanam-teri-kasam-2-opposite-harsvardhan-rane-netizens-react%2Farticleshow%2F118388268.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F118388268.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EFollowing%20the%20success%20of%20Stree%202%2C%20Shraddha%20Kapoor%20is%20rumored%20to%20be%20consi