Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20couple%20of%20years%2C%C2%A0my%20husband%20and%20I%20lived%20with%20his%20family%20in%20a%20300-square-foot%20studio%20apartment%20that%20we%20built%20in%20his%20parents'%20garage%20in%20Hesperia%2C%20California%2C%20about%20two%20hours%20outside%20San%20Diego.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20time%2C%20buying%20a%20house%20wasn't%20even%20on%20the%20table%2C%20and%20studio%20apartments%20were%20going%20for%20about%20%242%2C000%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20very%20thankful%20for%20the%20opportunity%20to%20live%20with%20my%20in-laws%2C%20as%20they%20charged%20us%20very%20little%20rent%2C%20which%20helped%20us%20grow%20our%20savings.%20However%2C%20his%20parents%20had%20a%20full%20house%2C%20and%20although%20we%20had%20our%20own%20space%2C%20it%20felt%20cramped%20with%20little%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20getting%20married%20in%202022%2C%20we%20started%20thinking%20about%20starting%20a%20family.%20We%20realized%20that%20to%20find%20an%20affordable%20home%20with%20enough%20space%20and%20build%20our%20own%20life%2C%20we'd%20have%20to%20leave%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Sundbergs%20at%20a%20California%20beach.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ab6e47eb4be2fff9a439c0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Sundbergs%20at%20a%20California%20beach.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kaitlyn%20Sundberg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20really%20hoping%20to%20move%20to%20places%20like%20Washington%20state%2C%20South%20Carolina%2C%20Oregon%2C%20Northern%20California%2C%20Utah%2C%20Colorado%2C%20or%20even%20Arizona.%20My%20husband%20applied%20for%20jobs%20in%20those%20states%2C%20but%20no%20opportunities%20came%20up.%20We%20also%20looked%20at%20housing%20in%20those%20areas%2C%20and%20many%20had%20prices%20similar%20to%20what%20we%20were%20seeing%20in%20Southern%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20Jack%20found%20a%20job%20he%20really%20liked.%20After%20telling%20me%20all%20the%20positives%2C%20he%20finally%20mentioned%20it%20was%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-cost-of-living-nyc-kansas-city-midwest-rent-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKansas%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20one%20of%20the%20states%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20move%20to%20because%20I%20was%20afraid%20of%20tornadoes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20I%20told%20him%2C%20%26quot%3BGo%20ahead%2C%20go%20for%20it.%20What's%20the%20worst%20that%20could%20happen%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20applied%20for%20the%20job.%20The%20following%20week%2C%20they%20flew%20him%20out%20for%20an%20interview%2C%20and%20two%20months%20later%2C%20we%20moved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d243f63a-0b83-49e7-94a4-54f82afe8219%5C%22%3EWe%20found%20the%20perfect%20home%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20we%20were%20living%20in%20an%20apartment%20in%20Wichita.%20Eventually%2C%20we%20started%20looking%20for%20a%20home%2C%20which%20felt%20like%20a%20big%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20drew%20a%20large%20square%20on%20the%20map%20and%20began%20searching%20on%20Realtor.com.%20We'd%20find%20houses%20we%20liked%2C%20but%20by%20the%20next%20day%2C%20they'd%20be%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20eventually%20found%20a%20home%20in%20Neodesha%20that%20I%20really%20liked.%20We%20called%20our%20real-estate%20agent%2C%20who%20agreed%20to%20meet%20us%20at%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20drove%20through%20Neodesha%2C%20we%20saw%20a%20softball%20game%2C%20kids%20riding%20their%20bikes%2C%20and%20the%20neighborhood%20pool%20full.%20It%20had%20such%20a%20great%20hometown%20vibe.%20I%20teared%20up%20in%20the%20car%20%E2%80%94%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20scene%20from%20a%20movie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20pulled%20up%20to%20the%20house%20and%20walked%20in%2C%20it%20was%20another%20moment%20of%20tears.%20It%20felt%20like%20trying%20on%20a%20wedding%20dress%20%E2%80%94%20everything%20seemed%20so%20perfect%20and%20fit%20so%20well.%20We%20put%20an%20offer%20on%20the%20house%20that%20day%2C%20and%20it%20was%20accepted%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22657%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kaitlyn%20and%20Jack%20Sundberg%20with%20their%20dogs%20in%20front%20of%20their%20home.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ab5fa57bb3f854015c7557%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22816%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Sundbergs%20and%20their%20dogs.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kaitlyn%20Sundberg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20paid%20%24240%2C000%20for%20the%20home.%20It's%20a%20four-bedroom%2C%20two-bathroom%20ranch-style%20house%20with%20about%202%2C300%20square%20feet%2C%20and%20we're%20on%20roughly%200.7%20acres.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe'd%20never%20be%20able%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20as%20nice%20as%20this%20one%20in%20California.%20I%20looked%20into%20it%2C%20and%20our%20Neodesha%20house%20is%20comparable%20to%20an%20%24800%2C000%20or%20%24900%2C000%20home%20in%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20is%20much%20better%20here.%20We're%20saving%20thousands%20a%20month%20on%20housing%20compared%20to%20what%20we%20would%20have%20paid%20in%20California.%20Gas%20and%20groceries%20are%20much%20cheaper%20as%20well%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-of-seven-how-to-combat-rising-prices-groceries-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeven%20with%20recent%20price%20increases%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20we've%20been%20saving%20by%20eating%20out%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220a69fa19-c961-4536-b3ee-221aa3e422db%5C%22%3EIt%20took%20time%20to%20adjust%20to%20small-town%20living%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENeodesha%20is%20a%20small%20town%20with%20about%202%2C000%20people.%20The%20closest%20big%20cities%20are%20Wichita%2C%20Kansas%20City%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-paid-to-move-from-la-to-tulsa-pros-cons-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETulsa%2C%20Oklahoma%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20all%20about%20one%20and%20a%20half%20to%20two%20hours%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20definitely%20a%20culture%20shock%20coming%20from%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20my%20dad%20was%20in%20the%20Coast%20Guard%2C%20so%20I%20moved%20around%20a%20lot%20and%20was%20used%20to%20adapting%20to%20new%20environments.%20Even%20still%2C%20I%20remember%20going%20to%20the%20grocery%20store%20in%20Neodesha%20and%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20do%20these%20people%20want%20to%20know%20my%20whole%20life%20story%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20just%20wanted%20to%20buy%20my%20oranges%20and%20get%20out%20of%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20slowly%20and%20surely%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20started%20warming%20up%20to%20it.%20Now%20one%20of%20my%20favorite%20things%20is%20just%20talking%20to%20people%20and%20getting%20to%20know%20everyone.%20It's%20nice%20to%20know%20that%20everyone%20looks%20out%20for%20each%20other%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225e3d9acf-e855-4682-9030-7c7069250f96%5C%22%3EI've%20made%20a%20life%20for%20myself%20here%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20graduated%20with%20my%20bachelor's%20in%20Liberal%20Studies%2C%20focusing%20on%20elementary%20education.%20When%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20moved%20to%20Kansas%2C%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20am%20I%20going%20to%20do%20now%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20worked%20as%20the%20director%20of%20a%20childcare%20center%20in%20Iowa%2C%20Kansas%20%E2%80%94%20about%20an%20hour's%20drive%20from%20our%20house%20in%20Neodesha.%20I%20was%20commuting%20an%20hour%20there%20and%20an%20hour%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20my%20neighbor%20shared%20a%20job%20posting%20for%20an%20early%20learning%20center%20opening%20just%20around%20the%20corner%20from%20my%20house.%20I%20applied%20for%20the%20director%20position%20and%20got%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20role%2C%20I've%20been%20involved%20in%20everything%20from%20the%20building%20process%20to%20ordering%20furniture%2C%20hiring%20teachers%2C%20enrolling%20students%2C%20and%20helping%20open%20the%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20learning%20center%20in%20Neodesha%2C%20Kansas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ab5ffd7bb3f854015c7560%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20early%20learning%20center%20in%20Neodesha%2C%20Kansas%2C%20where%20Sundberg%20works.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kaitlyn%20Sundberg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20joined%20the%20Neodesha%20Area%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%20and%20now%20sit%20on%20its%20board%2C%20which%20has%20really%20helped%20me%20get%20to%20know%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20go%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20community%20events%20and%20see%20parents%20and%20kids%20every%20day.%20Now%20I%20can't%20go%20anywhere%20without%20running%20into%20someone%20I%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20small-town%20thing%2C%20and%20I%20love%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2286ce220e-90c3-4416-9cb8-70a99d68bf86%5C%22%3EWe%20love%20small-town%20life%20but%20miss%20some%20big-city%20amenities%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20we%20moved%2C%20my%20mom%20was%20worried%20about%20tornadoes%20in%20Kansas.%20But%20having%20lived%20in%20so%20many%20places%20and%20experienced%20nearly%20every%20natural%20disaster%20%E2%80%94%20hurricanes%2C%20blizzards%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-california-wildfires-for-indiana-will-never-move-back-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efire%20days%20in%20California%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20I%20wasn't%20too%20concerned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20burn%20piles%20in%20Neodesha%20stressed%20me%20out%2C%20but%20over%20time%2C%20I've%20felt%20safer.%20Tornadoes%20are%20less%20common%20here%2C%20and%20although%20I%20still%20lock%20myself%20in%20the%20closet%20during%20warnings%2C%20I%20feel%20it's%20a%20quick%20event%20with%20enough%20notice%20before%20they%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHonestly%2C%20I%20haven't%20found%20much%20to%20dislike%20about%20Neodesha%2C%20except%20that%20people%20I%20know%20well%20see%20me%20around%20town%20without%20makeup%20on%20the%20weekends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20it%20would%20be%20nice%20to%20see%20more%20shops%20on%20Main%20Street%20%E2%80%94%20little%20boutiques%2C%20mom-and-pop%20stores%2C%20and%20more%20restaurants.%20That's%20something%20we%2C%20coming%20from%20California%2C%20really%20miss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20few%20more%20businesses%20would%20be%20great.%20It%20would%20help%20bring%20more%20people%20into%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20no%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinance.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Ftarget-10-insider-secrets-know-150052688.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETarget%3C%2Fa%3E%20nearby%2C%20so%20more%20options%20for%20shopping%20would%20be%20nice%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d3be1044-86b8-41dd-9022-cbb9f4682f9f%5C%22%3EWe're%20never%20moving%20back%20to%20California%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKansas%20truly%20feels%20like%20home%20in%20a%20way%20California%20never%20really%20did.%20I%20feel%20like%20my%20husband%2C%20and%20I%20have%20come%20into%20our%20own%20and%20have%20established%20a%20life%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20plan%20on%20staying%20in%20Neodesha.%20We%20think%20it's%20a%20great%20place%20to%20raise%20kids.%20I%20also%20love%20my%20job.%20I%20helped%20build%20the%20learning%20center%20and%20told%20my%20husband%20he'd%20have%20to%20drag%20me%20out%20of%20this%20town%20because%20it%20feels%20like%20my%20baby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20tough%20being%20away%20from%20family.%20But%20my%20in-laws%20love%20it%20here%2C%20and%20we're%20doing%20our%20best%20to%20convince%20them%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20our%20family%20%E2%80%94%20to%20move%20here%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Sundbergs%20at%20a%20baseball%20game.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ab61d56630eb10385c337c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Sundbergs%20at%20a%20baseball%20game%20in%20Kansas%20City.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kaitlyn%20Sundberg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20honestly%20don't%20know%20how%20Jack%20and%20I%20lived%20in%20California%20for%20so%20long.%20Unless%20we%20were%20being%20paid%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20we'd%20ever%20move%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20visited%20recently%2C%20and%20I%20hated%20it.%20There%20were%20people%20everywhere%2C%20and%20they%20weren't%20as%20friendly.%20When%20I%20went%20to%20Target%2C%20I%20was%20the%20weirdo%20smiling%20and%20trying%20to%20talk%20to%20everyone%2C%20but%20no%20one%20was%20having%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20driving%20in%20California%20stressed%20me%20out.%20The%20worst%20traffic%20in%20Neodesha%20is%20getting%20stuck%20behind%20a%20tractor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaving-california-moved-to-kansas-bought-home-money-goes-farther-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739957582000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ab5f4feb4be2fff9a437b1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaving-california-moved-to-kansas-bought-home-money-goes-farther-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kaitlyn%20Sundberg%20and%20her%20husband%20left%20California%20for%20a%20better%20shot%20at%20homeownership.%20She%20said%20they%20bought%20a%20house%20in%20Kansas%20and%20are%20happier%20than%20ever.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22alloyd%40insider.com%20(Alcynna%20Lloyd)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A55%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaving-california-moved-to-kansas-bought-home-money-goes-fart