20are%20projected%20to%20deliver%20another%20half%20a%20million%20new%20apartments%20this%20year%2C%20down%20slightly%20from%202024%2C%20which%20should%20force%20property%20managers%20to%20focus%20on%20keeping%20their%20buildings%20full%20instead%20of%20jacking%20up%20rents.%20The%20outlook%20for%20renters%2C%20though%2C%20turns%20gloomier%20once%20you%20look%20at%202026%20and%20beyond.%20Apartment%20supply%20boomed%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20but%20demand%20kept%20pace%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20no%20glut%20of%20empty%20units.%20And%20the%20construction%20pipeline%20has%20slimmed%20down%20significantly%20since%20the%20glory%20days%20of%20cheap%20money%2C%20when%20it%20was%20easier%20for%20developers%20to%20secure%20loans%20for%20new%20projects.%20While%20plenty%20of%20rentals%20opened%20their%20doors%20in%202024%2C%20apartment%20builders%20broke%20ground%20on%20the%20fewest%20units%20in%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20available%20inventory%20of%20rental%20housing%20units%20may%20quickly%20tighten%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20a%20recent%20report%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapartment-rent-increases-landlords-antitrust-lawsuits-real-estate-software-realpage-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERealPage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20software%20company%20that%20helps%20landlords%20set%20their%20rents.%20The%20real%20estate%20analytics%20firm%20Yardi%20Matrix%20has%20characterized%202025%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Byear%20fraught%20with%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETranslation%3A%20Snag%20those%20apartment%20deals%20while%20you%20can.%20They%20probably%20won't%20last%20much%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20past%20few%20years%20have%20been%20chaotic%20for%20apartment%20dwellers.%20Demand%20for%20apartments%20soared%20in%202021%20as%20renters%20upgraded%20to%20bigger%20places%2C%20moved%20out%20of%20their%20parents'%20houses%2C%20or%20said%20goodbye%20to%20roommates%20in%20favor%20of%20solo%20living.%20This%20surge%20in%20%26quot%3Bhousehold%20formation%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-apartment-rent-high-pandemic-big-cities-household-formation-roommates-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epushed%20up%20rents%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20as%20people%20decamped%20from%20crowded%20cities%20to%20single-family%20homes%20in%20the%20suburbs.%20Zillow%20found%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-rent-hikes-impacted-city-residents-covid-deals-la-nyc-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapartment%20rents%20rose%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20more%20than%2020%25%20nationally%20from%202020%20through%202022.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20though%2C%20developers%20were%20setting%20the%20stage%20for%20a%20reversal.%20At%20one%20point%20in%202022%2C%20more%20than%20a%20million%20new%20apartment%20units%20were%20under%20construction%20across%20the%20country.%20The%20rush%20of%20new%20builds%20came%20to%20fruition%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%3A%20According%20to%20RealPage%2C%20developers%20opened%20a%20total%20of%20440%2C000%20units%20in%202023%20and%20a%20record%20588%2C900%20last%20year%2C%20with%20another%20500%2C000%20expected%20to%20become%20available%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapartments-record-us-housing-affordability-crisis-home-prices-real-estate-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20buildings%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20kept%20prices%20in%20check%3B%20as%20the%20rental-housing%20economist%20Jay%20Parsons%20puts%20it%2C%20they%20%26quot%3Bdid%20what%20supply%20is%20supposed%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%20With%20lots%20of%20new%20units%20on%20the%20market%2C%20renters%20have%20more%20choices%20and%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20tolerate%20steep%20rent%20hikes.%20Yardi%20Matrix's%20data%20indicates%20year-over-year%20rent%20growth%20has%20stayed%20under%201%25%20over%20the%20past%2016%20months%2C%20well%20below%20the%20double-digit%20jumps%20of%202022.%20Landlord%20concessions%20%E2%80%94%20the%20months%20of%20free%20rent%2C%20free%20parking%2C%20and%20gift%20cards%20used%20to%20attract%20and%20retain%20tenants%20%E2%80%94%20are%20back%20in%20fashion.%20At%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20almost%2013%25%20of%20units%20nationwide%20were%20offering%20concessions%2C%20pretty%20close%20to%20the%20all-time%20highs%20from%20the%20early%20months%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20when%20hardly%20anyone%20wanted%20to%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20kinds%20of%20renters%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20the%20high%20earners%20who%20can%20afford%20the%20latest%20and%20greatest%20in%20apartment%20construction%20%E2%80%94%20have%20benefited%20from%20this%20development%20boom.%20Landlords%20typically%20roll%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmore-landlords-offer-rental-perks-concessions-free-rent-parking-nyc-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econcessions%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20they're%20trying%20to%20lease%20up%20new%20buildings%2C%20most%20of%20which%20are%20classified%20as%20%26quot%3Bluxury%26quot%3B%20these%20days.%20But%20even%20long-standing%20buildings%20with%20cheaper%20apartments%20have%20been%20offering%20freebies%20to%20keep%20tenants%20from%20fleeing%20for%20greener%20pastures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20a%20simple%20supply-and-demand%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20Carl%20Whitaker%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20RealPage%2C%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BAs%20more%20supply%20delivers%2C%20you%20have%20to%20draw%20more%20traffic%20to%20your%20property%2C%20and%20that%20comes%20with%20these%20incentives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trouble%20for%20renters%20is%20that%20property%20managers%20may%20soon%20find%20those%20efforts%20unnecessary.%20Developers%20rely%20heavily%20on%20debt%20to%20finance%20new%20projects%2C%20and%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-the-federal-funds-rate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterest-rate%20hikes%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20made%20those%20loans%20much%20more%20expensive%2C%20prompting%20a%20downturn%20in%20construction%20plans.%20Builders%20have%20been%20further%20deterred%20by%20the%20wave%20of%20new%20supply%20coming%20to%20market%20and%20the%20prospect%20of%20weaker%20rent%20growth%20at%20their%20properties.%20By%20doing%20so%2C%20they've%20laid%20the%20groundwork%20for%20another%20apartment%20shortage%20%E2%80%94%20and%20for%20rents%20to%20start%20climbing%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20pendulum%20is%20swinging%20dramatically%2C%26quot%3B%20Parsons%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20apartment%20construction%20has%20a%20tendency%20to%20be%20way%20too%20cyclical%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20think%20that's%20a%20great%20thing%20for%20renters%20or%20investors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EPredicting%20the%20economy's%20twists%20and%20turns%20may%20be%20hard%2C%20but%20forecasting%20new-apartment%20supply%20is%20pretty%20straightforward.%20If%20you%20know%20how%20many%20units%20are%20under%20construction%20today%2C%20you%20can%20reasonably%20estimate%20the%20new%20supply%20in%20a%20few%20years.%20These%20numbers%20point%20to%20a%20seismic%20shift%20in%20the%20rental%20landscape.%20Apartment%20construction%20starts%20dropped%20last%20year%20to%20the%20lowest%20level%20since%202013%2C%20per%20RealPage.%20This%20slowdown%20will%20soon%20start%20showing%20up%20in%20the%20number%20of%20new%20apartments%20coming%20to%20the%20market.%20Yardi%20Matrix%20expects%20524%2C000%20deliveries%20in%202025%2C%20but%20then%20only%20414%2C000%20in%202026%20and%20341%2C000%20the%20year%20after.%20RealPage%20anticipates%20an%20even%20steeper%20drop-off%2C%20from%20470%2C000%20new%20units%20this%20year%20to%20265%2C000%20in%202026%2C%20with%20another%20decline%20the%20following%20year.%20Christopher%20Bruen%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20National%20Multifamily%20Housing%20Council%2C%20wrote%20last%20year%20that%20this%20retreat%20was%20%26quot%3Blikely%20to%20exacerbate%20our%20nation's%20housing%20shortage%20over%20the%20longer%20term.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20cities%20won't%20feel%20the%20effects%20of%20this%20pullback%20equally.%20Most%20of%20the%20apartments%20built%20during%20this%20construction%20renaissance%20are%20in%20the%20lower%20half%20of%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20Austin%2C%20Atlanta%2C%20Phoenix%2C%20and%20Houston%2C%20among%20others.%20Some%20metros%20in%20the%20mountain%20region%2C%20such%20as%20Denver%20and%20Salt%20Lake%20City%2C%20have%20also%20welcomed%20a%20lot%20of%20new%20apartments.%20Rents%20in%20these%20markets%20may%20be%20slower%20to%20rise%20again%2C%20but%20housing%20demand%20in%20these%20areas%20has%20also%20been%20higher%20than%20in%20other%20places%20around%20the%20country%2C%20so%20the%20relative%20relief%20may%20be%20short-lived.%20As%20for%20major%20coastal%20markets%20like%20New%20York%2C%20Boston%2C%20Seattle%2C%20and%20San%20Francisco%2C%20where%20land%20availability%20and%20permitting%20hurdles%20already%20make%20it%20harder%20to%20build%20apartments%2C%20it%20could%20be%20even%20tougher%20for%20renters.%20In%20a%20recent%20earnings%20call%20with%20investors%2C%20an%20executive%20at%20Equity%20Residential%2C%20one%20of%20the%20nation's%20largest%20apartment%20owners%2C%20described%20the%20reduction%20in%20supply%20as%20%26quot%3Beven%20more%20dramatic%26quot%3B%20in%20these%20markets%2C%20where%20starts%20were%20down%20by%2030%25%20in%202023%20and%20by%20nearly%2060%25%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%202025%20starts%20projected%20to%20be%20down%20again%2C%20we%20anticipate%20one%20of%20the%20best%20supply-demand%20balances%20in%20our%20coastal%20markets%20that%20we%20have%20seen%20in%20a%20very%20long%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Alexander%20Brackenridge%2C%20the%20company's%20chief%20investment%20officer%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20complicating%20factor%20is%20construction%20delays.%20Doug%20Ressler%2C%20the%20manager%20of%20business%20intelligence%20at%20Yardi%20Matrix%2C%20says%20completions%20projected%20for%202025%20may%20bleed%20into%202026%20and%20even%202027%20because%20of%20supply-chain%20snags%20or%20labor%20shortages%2C%20easing%20the%20pain%20for%20renters.%20The%20company%20expects%20rents%20to%20rise%20by%20a%20modest%201.5%25%20this%20year%2C%20by%201.1%25%20in%202026%2C%20and%20then%20by%203.3%25%20in%202027.%20Parsons%20anticipates%20even%20bigger%20year-over-year%20growth%2C%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bmid-single%20digits%2C%26quot%3B%20starting%20in%202026.%20That%20kind%20of%20increase%20is%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20pandemic-era%20rent%20hikes%2C%20but%20it%20would%20still%20mean%20the%20end%20of%20this%20concession-laden%20era%20for%20renters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20demand%20for%20apartments%20really%20picks%20up%20%E2%80%94%20if%2C%20say%2C%20people%20feel%20better%20about%20their%20economic%20prospects%20or%20decide%20that%20renting%20will%20get%20them%20more%20bang%20for%20their%20buck%20than%20buying%20%E2%80%94%20rent%20growth%20could%20climb%20even%20higher.%20Whitaker%20tells%20me%20it's%20still%20too%20early%20in%20the%20year%20to%20tell%20how%20many%20renters%20will%20seek%20out%20new%20units%20during%20the%20peak%20summer%20months%2C%20but%20there%20are%20already%20signs%20that%20this%20year%20could%20be%20hotter%20than%20last.%20In%20both%20November%20and%20December%2C%20leasing%20traffic%20%E2%80%94%20the%20number%20of%20prospective%20renters%20checking%20out%20new%20apartments%20%E2%80%94%20increased%20from%20a%20year%20prior.%20That%20may%20sound%20ho-hum%2C%20but%20it%20was%20the%20first%20time%20since%20early%202022%20that%20leasing%20traffic%20notched%20two%20straight%20months%20of%20year-over-year%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20interpretation%20is%20that%20we%20are%20going%20to%20see%20quite%20a%20bit%20of%20demand%20this%20summer%2C%26quot%3B%20Whitaker%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAre%20we%20doomed%20to%20repeat%20these%20cycles%2C%20waiting%20for%20any%20bit%20of%20housing%20relief%20to%20be%20revealed%20as%20a%20mirage%3F%20Parsons%20doesn't%20think%20so.%20He%20points%20to%20a%20national%20construction%20fund%20%E2%80%94%20which%20could%20provide%20cheaper%20debt%20for%20developers%20so%20they're%20less%20likely%20to%20pull%20back%20when%20interest%20rates%20rise%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20bipartisan%20solution%20that%20could%20smooth%20out%20this%20rental%20roller%20coaster.%20Absent%20that%2C%20though%2C%20renters%20are%20staring%20down%20yet%20another%20bumpy%20ride.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20took%20a%20perfect%20storm%20of%20factors%20to%20drive%20this%20massive%20construction%20boom%2C%26quot%3B%20Parsons%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20now%20a%20lot%20of%20those%20factors%20have%20just%20gone%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frent-going-up-costs-apartment-construction-housing-shortage-landlord-concessions-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739956021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b4a00a6630eb10385cdc1a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frent-going-up-costs-apartment-construction-housing-shortage-landlord-concessions-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20historic%20wave%20of%20apartment%20construction%20is%20drawing%20to%20a%20close%2C%20which%20means%20rents%20may%20soon%20start%20rising%20again.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jrodriguez%40insider.com%20(James%20Rodriguez)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A22%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessins