%20US%20Air%20Force%20F-35%20Lightning%20II%20Joint%20Strike%20Fighters.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%2FStaff%20Sgt.%20Madelyn%20Brown%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELockheed%20Martin's%20F-35%20Lightning%20II%20is%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20advanced%20fighter%20jets.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBusiness%20Insider%20toured%20a%20facility%20where%20the%20stealth%20jet%20is%20made.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20production%20line%20in%20Fort%20Worth%2C%20Texas%2C%20is%20cranking%20out%20over%20150%20aircraft%20a%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20sprawling%20factory%20in%20Texas%2C%20thousands%20of%20people%20are%20working%20around%20the%20clock%20to%20assemble%20the%20US%20military's%20most%20advanced%20multi-role%20fighter%20jet%3A%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-strikes-iran-shows-f-35-ready-higher-level-war-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EF-35%20Lightning%20II%20Joint%20Strike%20Fighter.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20facility%2C%20operated%20by%20defense%20giant%20Lockheed%20Martin%2C%20stretches%20more%20than%20a%20mile%20and%20cranks%20out%20over%20150%20aircraft%20a%20year.%20It's%20enormous%2C%20with%20people%20riding%20golf%20carts%20or%20bikes%20to%20travel%20from%20one%20end%20to%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20recently%20toured%20the%20factory%2C%20officially%20called%20Air%20Force%20Plant%204.%20An%20overhead%20view%20of%20the%20production%20line%2C%20looking%20from%20right%20to%20left%2C%20reveals%20the%20tremendous%20scale%20of%20the%20operation.%20F-35s%20can%20be%20seen%20going%20from%20just%20the%20bare%20bones%20%E2%80%94%20chunks%20of%20metal%20largely%20unrecognizable%20to%20the%20untrained%20eye%20%E2%80%94%20to%20a%20jet%20that's%20nearly%20in%20its%20final%20form%3A%20a%20single-engine%2C%20supersonic%20stealth%20fighter%20jet%20made%20to%20dominate%20a%20range%20of%20combat%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20F-35%20is%20the%20world's%20most%20expensive%20weapons%20program%2C%20with%20an%20expected%20lifetime%20cost%20of%20more%20than%20%242%20trillion.%20Elon%20Musk%20and%20others%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-f-35-stealth-fighters-to-fly-less-costs-soar-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esharply%20criticized%20the%20aircraft%3C%2Fa%3E%20amid%20rising%20program%20costs%2C%20sustainability%20challenges%2C%20and%20developmental%20setbacks.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20constantly%20being%20upgraded%20and%20is%20widely%20recognized%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-china-us-militaries-fifth-gen-fighter-jets-problems-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etop%20fifth-generation%20fighter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELockheed%20says%20that%20production%20of%20the%20jet%20contributes%20roughly%20%2472%20billion%20annually%20to%20the%20US%20economy%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethrough%20its%20network%20of%20suppliers%20and%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20workers%20spread%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224851fe24-9850-42ce-acc1-d5abff88a1c8%5C%22%3EIt%20takes%20about%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20to%20build%20a%20new%20F-35%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAir%20Force%20Plant%204%20has%20been%20making%20warplanes%20for%20decades.%20It%20began%20producing%20bomber%20aircraft%20during%20World%20War%20II%20before%20transitioning%20to%20the%20now-retired%20F-111%20Aardvark%20in%20the%201960s.%20Several%20years%20later%2C%20it%20started%20building%20F-16s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20view%20of%20the%20F-35%20production%20line%20in%20Fort%20Worth%2C%20Texas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b4887f6630eb10385cda39%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20view%20of%20the%20F-35%20production%20line%20in%20Fort%20Worth%2C%20Texas.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Lockheed%20Martin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20F-35%20Joint%20Strike%20Fighter%20rolled%20off%20the%20factory%20floor%20in%202006%2C%20and%20since%20then%2C%20more%20than%201%2C110%20of%20these%20fighter%20jets%20have%20been%20delivered%20to%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20significant%20delays%2C%20the%20F-35%20program%20last%20year%20achieved%20full-rate%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20single%20F-35%20takes%20around%2018%20months%20to%20build%2C%20and%20this%20production%20facility%20can%20turn%20out%20156%20fighters%20annually%20from%20across%20all%20three%20variants%20%E2%80%94%20the%20A%2C%20B%2C%20and%20C%20variants%20are%20designed%20for%20conventional%20and%20ship-based%20take-off%20and%20landing.%20It%20is%20a%2024-hour-a-day%20operation%2C%20with%20thousands%20of%20workers%20moving%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20plant%20on%20any%20given%20day%2C%20surrounded%20by%20heavy%20machinery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20view%20of%20the%20F-35%20production%20line%20in%20Fort%20Worth%2C%20Texas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b489626630eb10385cda47%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnother%20view%20of%20the%20F-35%20production%20facility.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Lockheed%20Martin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBuilding%20the%20fighter%20jet%20starts%20with%20the%20assembly%20of%20its%20wing%20section.%20Constructing%20the%20airframe%20then%20moves%20down%20the%20production%20line%20to%20an%20area%20where%20the%20four%20major%20structure%20pieces%20of%20the%20jet%20%E2%80%94%20the%20tail%20section%2C%20wings%2C%20center%20fuselage%2C%20and%20forward%20fuselage%20%E2%80%94%20are%20brought%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2268a187e1-ec77-4ce3-b699-a679d983a8b3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaintaining%20a%20steady%20parts%20supply%20is%20a%20big%20challenge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20where%20the%20aircraft%20really%20starts%20to%20take%20its%20highly%20recognizable%20shape.%20Small%20screens%20next%20to%20the%20aircraft%20show%20which%20country%20it's%20being%20made%20for%3A%20a%20stroll%20down%20the%20production%20line%20reveals%20the%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20Poland%2C%20Israel%2C%20and%20Japan%2C%20to%20name%20a%20few.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225762%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20view%20of%20the%20F-35%20production%20line%20in%20Forth%20Worth%2C%20Texas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b489947bb3f854015d1c10%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223841%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnother%20angle%20showing%20the%20F-35%20production%20line.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Lockheed%20Martin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EParts%20for%20the%20F-35%20%E2%80%94%20of%20which%20there%20are%20thousands%20%E2%80%94%20come%20from%20all%20over%20the%20world%20because%20the%20jet%20is%20a%20multinational%20project.%20One%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20with%20building%20the%20fighter%2C%20BI%20learned%2C%20is%20ensuring%20that%20an%20adequate%20supply%20of%20parts%20is%20flowing%20to%20the%20Fort%20Worth%20production%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20fighters%20reach%20the%20end%20of%20the%20production%20line%2C%20they%20are%20ready%20to%20be%20painted%20their%20signature%20gray%20color.%20The%20paint%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company%2C%20is%20designed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.f35.com%2Ff35%2Fnews-and-features%2Fthe-f35s-unrivaled-stealth.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereduce%20and%20absorb%20radar%20signals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20contributes%20to%20the%20aircraft's%20stealth%20profile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20painting%20process%20happens%20in%20a%20separate%20building%20equipped%20with%20hangers%20that%20can%20close%20off%20during%20the%20coloring%20process.%20Some%20automation%20is%20involved%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20an%20F-35%20jet%2C%20including%20when%20building%20its%20wing%20structure%20and%20during%20the%20painting%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225469%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20completed%20US%20Air%20Force%20F-35%20is%20seen%20during%20an%20air%20show%20in%20February%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b48b476630eb10385cda63%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223646%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20completed%20US%20Air%20Force%20F-35%20is%20seen%20during%20an%20air%20show%20in%20February%202023.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FAijaz%20Rahi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20aircraft%20is%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftest-pilot-shares-experience-flying-f-16-and-f-35-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflown%20several%20times%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20part%20of%20testing%20before%20it%20is%20ready%20to%20be%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20largest%20F-35%20final%20assembly%20facility%20is%20in%20Fort%20Worth%2C%20but%20there%20is%20one%20smaller%20plant%20in%20Italy%20and%20another%20in%20Japan.%20These%20sites%20underline%20the%20global%20nature%20of%20the%20operation%2C%20as%20planes%20are%20shipped%20off%20to%20militaries%20in%20North%20America%2C%20Europe%2C%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20and%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20F-35%20has%20been%20used%20in%20combat%20since%20its%20first%20flight%20nearly%2020%20years%20ago.%20The%20US%20military%20has%20flown%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ff-35-variants-seen-combat-after-fighter-struck-houthis-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eall%20three%20variants%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20strike%20missions%20against%20terror%20groups%20in%20Iraq%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20and%20Yemen.%20The%20jet%20also%20received%20significant%20praise%20after%20Israel%20used%20it%20to%20carry%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-showed-power-of-f-35s-iran-strikes-uk-admiral-202